->Express.js is written in JavaScript, not TypeScript. When you use TypeScript with Express, you're essentially using:

TypeScript code that gets compiled to JavaScript
JavaScript libraries (Express) with TypeScript definitions bolted on top

-> add "type":"module" in package.json for the error of 
     ECMAScript imports and exports cannot be written in a CommonJS file under 'verbatimModuleSyntax'. 